data.meta_desc: In 2009 a furniture manufacturer in Belgium was about to celebrate their 25th anniversary. The owner told everyone to dress casual the next day that there would be a serious announcement and no work to be done. The nervous employees showed up to find the showroom completely empty except for a single leather sofa that they manufactured. The owner entered told them all how much he appreciated their work and announced that they were all getting raises under one condition , , , they had to eat the sofa. He then stabbed it with a large knife. Everyone enjoyed the cake and were then treated to a charter bus ride to a party hall for the real celebration. Not all bosses are assholes. Memes.
